# AI Builder Tool Executor (`lib/ai/tool-executor.ts`)

## Core Rule — Tool Behavior Must Mirror the Panel

Every executor function must write to exactly the same place as the builder's right-side panel control for that property. The panel's `patchStyle` path now calls `styleToClassName` before saving, so pixel inputs are stored as arbitrary-value Tailwind classes (e.g. `pt-[16px]`). The tool must do the same — write to `props.className`, never to `style.*` for pixel inputs.

See `ai-builder-knowledge.mdc` for the full alignment philosophy and audit process.

---

## Style Mechanism Decisions (How & Why Each Tool Writes)

### Inline Style vs Tailwind Class

**When to write to `props.className` (Tailwind arbitrary-value class):**
- Pixel-value controls (`NumberInput`): write as `pt-[Npx]`, `gap-[Npx]`, `max-w-[Npx]`, `top-[Npx]`, etc. — always strip the corresponding `style.*` key
- Token-value controls (`SelectInput`): write as a standard Tailwind utility like `shadow-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `font-bold`
- Colors: write as `bg-[#hex]`, `bg-[var(--...)]`, `text-[#hex]`, `border-[#hex]`, etc.

**When to write to `style.*` (inline style) — exceptions only:**
- `transform: rotate(Ndeg)` — degrees don't map cleanly to a Tailwind class
- `px:N` exact width/height — double-write BOTH `w-[Npx]` class AND `style.width = "Npx"` to guard against stale `defaultNode` inline styles winning
- `style.opacity` — panel reads directly from `style.opacity`; no class form

**Why this changed from the old model:** The panel's `patchStyle` now runs `styleToClassName` before saving — pixel inputs like `padding: 24` become `pt-[24px] pr-[24px] pb-[24px] pl-[24px]` in `props.className` and `props.style` is cleared of those keys. Both panel and tool now use the same storage format. At render time, `classToInlineStyle()` in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx` converts arbitrary-value classes back to inline styles so the browser renders them correctly (NativeWind's JIT scanner can't see dynamic classes from JSON).

**When to write both `props.className` AND `style.*`:**
- `set_size` with `px:N` values: double-write guards against `defaultNode` inline style winning

---

## Tool-by-Tool Decisions

### `set_spacing`
- Writes to `props.className` as arbitrary-value classes: `pt-[Npx]`, `pr-[Npx]`, `pb-[Npx]`, `pl-[Npx]`, `mx-[Npx]`, `gap-[Npx]`, etc.
- Values are **pixels** — input `p: 24` becomes `pt-[24px] pr-[24px] pb-[24px] pl-[24px]`
- Strips bare shorthands (`p-4`, `m-8`) and side-specific classes (`pt-*`, `gap-*`) before writing — prevents conflicts with primitive defaults
- Zero value (`p: 0`, `gap: 0`) strips existing classes without writing a zero-value class — zero padding/gap = no class needed
- Strips corresponding `style.*` keys (`paddingTop`, `gap`, etc.) so inline styles from old code don't conflict
- **Why classes:** The panel's `patchStyle` now calls `styleToClassName` before saving — both panel and tool write arbitrary-value classes, keeping them in sync

### `set_layout.gap`
- Gap writes `gap-[Npx]` to `props.className` — same pattern as `set_spacing`
- Strips any existing `gap-*` class and `style.gap` key
- `buildLayoutClass()` helper is gap-unaware; gap handling happens after it returns in the executor
- **Why classes:** Same reason as `set_spacing` — panel now writes classes, not `style.gap`

### `set_opacity`
- Writes to `style.opacity` as a 0–1 float (input 0–100 → divided by 100)
- Strips any `opacity-*` Tailwind class
- `opacity: 100` → removes the `opacity` style key entirely (fully visible = no override needed)
- **Why:** The panel opacity slider → `patchStyle({ opacity: "0.8" })`

### `set_position` inset (top/right/bottom/left)
- Writes `top-[Npx]`, `right-[Npx]`, `bottom-[Npx]`, `left-[Npx]` to `props.className`
- Strips corresponding `style.*` keys (`top`, `right`, `bottom`, `left`)
- position type and zIndex still use standard Tailwind token classes (`absolute`, `z-10`, etc.)
- **Why classes:** Same migration as `set_spacing` — panel writes arbitrary-value classes, not `style.*`

### `set_transform` rotate
- Writes to `style.transform = "rotate(Ndeg)"` — any degree value, not limited to Tailwind's preset values
- Strips any `rotate-*` / `-rotate-*` Tailwind classes
- `rotate: 0` → removes the `transform` style key
- **Why:** Rotate in the panel is a `NumberInput` (-180 to 180) → `patchStyle({ transform: "rotate(Ndeg)" })`
- flipX/flipY still use Tailwind classes (`-scale-x-100` etc.) because the panel uses a toggle that writes a class

### `set_size`
- `width` / `height` named modes (`full`, `fit`, `fill`, `screen`, `min-screen`) → standard Tailwind token classes (`w-full`, `h-fit`, `flex-1`, `h-screen`, `min-h-screen`)
- `maxWidth`, `minWidth`, `maxHeight`, `minHeight` → write `max-w-[Npx]`, `min-w-[Npx]`, etc. to `props.className`; strip conflicting classes AND `style.*` keys; zero values strip without writing
- `px:N` exact width/height → **double-write**: `w-[Npx]` class AND `style.width = "Npx"` (guards against stale defaultNode inline styles)
- **Why classes for min/max:** Same migration as `set_spacing`

### `set_border` radius
- `"default"` → `rounded` (bare default Tailwind border-radius token)
- Per-corner `"default"` → bare `rounded-tl` / `rounded-tr` / etc.
- **Why:** The panel's `ROUNDED_TOKENS` array includes the bare `"rounded"` token

### `set_shadow`
- `"default"` → `shadow` (bare default Tailwind shadow token, between none and sm)
- **Why:** The panel's `SHADOW_TOKENS` array includes the bare `"shadow"` token

### `set_submit`
- Writes `props.type = "submit"` (true) or removes it (false)
- **Why:** The panel Settings has a "Submit" toggle that sets `props.type = "submit"` on a Button so it triggers FormContainer. The old tool controlled `props.action` (visual variant) — a completely different prop

### `set_input_props` type
- `"decimal"` → writes `props.type = "number"` + `props.step = "0.01"`
- Removed: `"url"`, `"search"`, `"date"` (not in the panel's Settings input type dropdown)
- **Why:** Matches the panel's actual type options exactly

